### User APIs - REST Client Testing
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or Thunder Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Setup: Get a valid JWT token first
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Register a test user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User One",
  "email": "testuser1@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123",
  "confirmPassword": "TestPassword123"
}

### Register another test user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Johnson",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "AlicePassword123",
  "confirmPassword": "AlicePassword123"
}

### Register third user for search testing
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob Smith",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "BobPassword123",
  "confirmPassword": "BobPassword123"
}

### Login to get token (use one of the emails above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser1@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 1. GET ALL USERS (DISCOVER)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get all users (default pagination - 20 per page)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get all users with custom limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?limit=5
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get all users with offset (pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?limit=10&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get next page of users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?limit=10&offset=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get single page (small limit for testing)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?limit=2&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 2. SEARCH USERS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Search by name (simple)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=alice
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Search by email
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=bob@example.com
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Search with partial name
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=john
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Search case-insensitive
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=ALICE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Search with pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=test&limit=5&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Search with limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=Smith&limit=2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 3. GET USER PROFILE BY ID
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get specific user profile (replace with real ObjectId)
### First, search to get a user ID, then use it here
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/507f1f77bcf86cd799439011
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### ERROR CASES & VALIDATION
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Search without query parameter
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Search with empty query
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Search with query too short (only 1 char)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=a
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Search with query too long (more than 100 chars)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Invalid user ID format
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/invalid-id
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Non-existent user ID (valid format)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/000000000000000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTHENTICATION ERRORS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### No authorization header
GET {{baseUrl}}/users

### Invalid token
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer invalid-token-here

### Malformed token
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.invalid.signature

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### PAGINATION TESTING
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Pagination with invalid limit (negative)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?limit=-5
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Pagination with invalid offset (negative)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?offset=-1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Pagination with limit exceeding max (>100)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?limit=150
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Pagination with non-numeric values (should use defaults)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?limit=abc&offset=xyz
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### NOTES
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###
### 1. Replace {{token}} with actual JWT token from login response
###    Example: Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
###
### 2. Replace user IDs with actual MongoDB ObjectIds from your database
###    Get them from search results or getAllUsers responses
###
### 3. Expected behavior:
###    - Current logged-in user never appears in results
###    - Search is case-insensitive
###    - Results sorted: users by creation date descending, search by name ascending
###    - Pagination: hasMore indicates if more results available
###
### 4. Response format:
###    {
###      "success": true/false,
###      "data": { /* response data */ },
###      "message": "Success or error message",
###      "statusCode": 200/400/401/404
###    }
###
### 5. Safe fields returned (sensitive fields excluded):
###    - _id, name, email, avatar, lastSeen, createdAt
###    - Never: password, __v, or internal fields
###
